## Objective
Fix the menu PDF download feature that currently generates HTML files instead of proper PDF documents, by implementing a robust PDF generation solution.

## Current Implementation Analysis
- The current implementation in `pdf-generator.tsx` (lines 91-100) creates and downloads an HTML file named `deskohub-menu.html` instead of a proper PDF.
- This approach doesn't meet user expectations when they request a PDF download.

## Implementation Steps

1. **Select and Install PDF Generation Library**:
   ```bash
   # Option 1: jsPDF for client-side PDF generation
   npm install jspdf html2canvas

   # Option 2: react-pdf for React-based PDF generation
   npm install @react-pdf/renderer
   ```

2. **Update PDF Generator Component**:
   ```typescript
   // features/menu/components/pdf-generator.tsx

   // Option 1: Using jsPDF
   import jsPDF from 'jspdf';
   import html2canvas from 'html2canvas';

   export const generateMenuPDF = async (menuElement: HTMLElement) => {
     try {
       // Create a new jsPDF instance
       const pdf = new jsPDF('p', 'mm', 'a4');

       // Convert the menu HTML element to canvas
       const canvas = await html2canvas(menuElement, {
         scale: 2, // Higher scale for better quality
         useCORS: true, // Enable loading of cross-origin images
         logging: false,
       });

       // Calculate dimensions to fit on A4
       const imgData = canvas.toDataURL('image/png');
       const imgWidth = 210; // A4 width in mm
       const pageHeight = 295; // A4 height in mm
       const imgHeight = (canvas.height * imgWidth) / canvas.width;

       // Add image to PDF
       pdf.addImage(imgData, 'PNG', 0, 0, imgWidth, imgHeight);

       // If content spans multiple pages, handle pagination
       let heightLeft = imgHeight;
       let position = 0;

       while (heightLeft > 0) {
         position = heightLeft - imgHeight;
         pdf.addPage();
         pdf.addImage(imgData, 'PNG', 0, position, imgWidth, imgHeight);
         heightLeft -= pageHeight;
       }

       // Save the PDF
       pdf.save('deskohub-menu.pdf');

       return true;
     } catch (error) {
       console.error('Error generating PDF:', error);
       return false;
     }
   };
   ```

3. **Alternative Implementation with react-pdf**:
   ```typescript
   // features/menu/components/pdf-generator.tsx
   import { Document, Page, Text, View, StyleSheet, PDFDownloadLink } from '@react-pdf/renderer';
   import { MenuCategory, MenuItem } from '@/types/menu';

   // Define styles for PDF document
   const styles = StyleSheet.create({
     page: {
       flexDirection: 'column',
       backgroundColor: '#FFFFFF',
       padding: 30,
     },
     section: {
       margin: 10,
       padding: 10,
     },
     categoryTitle: {
       fontSize: 18,
       fontWeight: 'bold',
       marginBottom: 10,
     },
     menuItem: {
       marginBottom: 10,
     },
     itemName: {
       fontSize: 14,
       fontWeight: 'bold',
     },
     itemDescription: {
       fontSize: 12,
       marginTop: 3,
     },
     itemPrice: {
       fontSize: 12,
       marginTop: 3,
     },
     allergens: {
       fontSize: 10,
       marginTop: 3,
       fontStyle: 'italic',
     },
   });

   // Create PDF Document component
   const MenuPDF = ({ categories }: { categories: MenuCategory[] }) => (
     <Document>
       <Page size="A4" style={styles.page}>
         {categories.map((category) => (
           <View key={category.id} style={styles.section}>
             <Text style={styles.categoryTitle}>{category.name}</Text>
             {category.items.map((item: MenuItem) => (
               <View key={item.id} style={styles.menuItem}>
                 <Text style={styles.itemName}>{item.name}</Text>
                 <Text style={styles.itemDescription}>{item.description}</Text>
                 <Text style={styles.itemPrice}>{item.price} Kč</Text>
                 {item.allergens && (
                   <Text style={styles.allergens}>
                     Allergens: {item.allergens.join(', ')}
                   </Text>
                 )}
               </View>
             ))}
           </View>
         ))}
       </Page>
     </Document>
   );

   // PDF Download Link component
   export const MenuPDFDownloadButton = ({ categories }: { categories: MenuCategory[] }) => (
     <PDFDownloadLink
       document={<MenuPDF categories={categories} />}
       fileName="deskohub-menu.pdf"
       className="btn btn-primary"
     >
       {({ loading }) => (loading ? 'Generating PDF...' : 'Download Menu PDF')}
     </PDFDownloadLink>
   );
   ```

4. **Update Menu Page to Use the New PDF Generator**:
   ```typescript
   // app/[locale]/menu/page.tsx
   import { MenuPDFDownloadButton } from '@/features/menu/components/pdf-generator';

   // Inside the Menu component
   return (
     <div>
       <div className="flex justify-between items-center mb-6">
         <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold">{t('menu.title')}</h1>
         <MenuPDFDownloadButton categories={menuCategories} />
       </div>
       {/* Rest of the menu component */}
     </div>
   );
   ```

5. **Handle Internationalization for PDF Content**:
   - Ensure the PDF generator respects the current locale
   - Include translations for all text elements in the PDF
   - Format prices according to locale conventions

6. **Add Loading State and Error Handling**:
   - Implement a loading indicator during PDF generation
   - Add proper error handling with user-friendly error messages
   - Provide fallback options if PDF generation fails

## Considerations
- **Performance**: PDF generation can be resource-intensive, especially for large menus. Consider implementing optimizations or potentially moving generation to the server side.
- **Styling**: Ensure the PDF styling matches the website's branding and design system.
- **Accessibility**: Include metadata in the PDF for better accessibility.
- **Browser Compatibility**: Test PDF generation across different browsers and devices.
- **File Size**: Optimize images and content to keep PDF file sizes reasonable.

