## Security Considerations

### Webhook Signature Verification
All webhooks are verified using HMAC signatures to ensure they come from trusted sources:

```typescript
// Example of signature verification
export function validateWebhookSignature(
  signature: string | null,
  payload: string,
  secret: string
): Effect<never, WebhookSignatureError, void> {
  return Effect.gen(function* (_) {
    if (!signature) {
      return yield* _(Effect.fail(new WebhookSignatureError()));
    }

    const computedSignature = yield* _(Effect.try({
      try: () => {
        const hmac = createHmac('sha256', secret);
        hmac.update(payload);
        return `sha256=${hmac.digest('hex')}`;
      },
      catch: () => new WebhookSignatureError()
    }));

    if (computedSignature !== signature) {
      return yield* _(Effect.fail(new WebhookSignatureError()));
    }

    return yield* _(Effect.succeed(void 0));
  });
}
```

### Secret Management
Webhook secrets are stored securely in environment variables and never exposed in client-side code:

```typescript
// Example of accessing webhook secrets
const webhookSecret = process.env.WEBHOOK_SECRET_KEY;
if (!webhookSecret) {
  throw new Error("WEBHOOK_SECRET_KEY environment variable is not set");
}
```

### Rate Limiting
The webhook API implements rate limiting to prevent abuse:

```typescript
// Example of rate limiting middleware
import { Ratelimit } from "@upstash/ratelimit";
import { Redis } from "@upstash/redis";

const ratelimit = new Ratelimit({
  redis: Redis.fromEnv(),
  limiter: Ratelimit.slidingWindow(10, "1m"),
  analytics: true,
});

// In the webhook route handler
const ip = request.headers.get("x-forwarded-for") ?? "127.0.0.1";
const { success, limit, reset, remaining } = await ratelimit.limit(ip);

if (!success) {
  return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "Too many requests" }), {
    status: 429,
    headers: {
      "X-RateLimit-Limit": limit.toString(),
      "X-RateLimit-Remaining": remaining.toString(),
      "X-RateLimit-Reset": reset.toString(),
    },
  });
}
```

### Input Sanitization
All webhook payloads are strictly validated against predefined schemas to prevent injection attacks and ensure data integrity.

